Chairman of Pinnacle Communications Ltd,  a leading broadcast technology company, Sir Lucky Omoluwa is dead. According to a family source, the broadcast technology investor and golf icon passed away at the National Hospital, Abuja,  in the early hours of  yesterday. Omoluwa was said to have taken ill on Saturday and was admitted at a hospital. He was said to have been discharged after showing signs of improvement. The deceased reportedly resumed work on Monday but suffered a relapse yesterday morning. Omoluwa reportedly died while undergoing treatment. The late Omoluwa was an illustrious entrepreneur and founder of Pinnacle Communications Ltd, a Nigerian broadcast engineering company which he headed until his demise. Omoluwa’s Pinnacle Communications is the only private licensed national signals distributor in the switchover from analogue to digital broadcasting in  Nigeria, and has invested multi-billion naira equipment for the actualisation of the project. Pinnacle has consistently won international awards from Nigeria, Ghana, the UK and USA companies in the areas of international best business practice, performance and commitment to commercial relationships and trade between the USA and Nigeria. Sir Lucky, who was knighted by Pope Benedict in 2010, is on the board of several companies with interests cutting across construction, oil and gas services as well as international procurements. He  was awarded a special congressional recognition by the US Congress in Washington DC in 2012.